name: Mogollon Monster 100
description:
Finished somewhere around top 10, need to confirm. Heat was killer the first day and the finish on the second. Took about five hours to get hydrated again after the 10 miles below the rim and the climb during mid afternoon.  

Horrible nausea kicked in around 85; tried to blast through but heat, dehydration, and nausea are a tough combination. Was definitely close to 100F on the slopes.

Also had horrible gastro issues of a different kind in the first 20 miles. Lost about 20 minutes making unplanned stops :/

Trail was super rugged and washed out almost everywhere. Jeff Browning blew the field away by hours.
